                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/73: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-27T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 27, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 27—6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>381. 1. Following from American Consul General at Mukden.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“March 27, 9 a.m. The new Chinese Mayor of Mukden, appointed by Provincial
                        Government, has invited consular corps and staffs to dinner at Yamato Hotel
                        on March 29th. My British colleague has accepted while some others are
                        undecided. Unless Legation disapproves my staff will accept. I am having
                        another engagement. Request immediate instructions.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>2. <persName corresp="#p_MMS1">Myers</persName> is being informed neither he nor
                    members of consular staff should accept such invitation unless with the
                    Department’s express approval. Please instruct Mukden direct.<note n="32"
                        xml:id="d680fn32">The Department instructed the Consul General at Mukden in
                        telegram of March 27, 1 p.m.: “Department approves your plan: your staff
                        accept, you decline.”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
